description_en: Helped to organize the groups members and activities.
Understanding what was required of the group and of the individual group members.
Suggesting ideas upon which the group could act or continue to build productively.
Coming up with something useful to contribute to the groups efforts.
Performing tasks allocated by the group within the specified timeframe.

Establishing standards for quality and evaluating group performance and decisions in relation to these standards.
Delivering constructive criticism.
Valuing the contributions of teammates; maintaining a positive attitude and encouraging a positive attitude in teammates.
Facilitating communications between teammates; helping members understand one another.
Contributing ideas and suggestions to the group.
Bringing new and relevant information to the group.
Interpreting, consolidating and integrating ideas and information into a useful result.
Accepting suggested tasks and/or volunteering for new ones.

Performing assigned tasks on time and/or notifying the group in a timely  fashion when assigned tasks cannot be completed for any reason (e.g. wrong task, insufficient information, insufficient time, etc.)\n
Asking questions relevant to understanding the groups goals or how to achieve  them. This includes questions aimed at understanding teammates ideas and  suggestions.\n
Representing or demonstrating the groups progress, goals and/or positions  effectively and accurately to non-members (orally, visually or otherwise).\n
Managing the development of, adherence to and revision of the groups specific timeline.
Suggesting allocation of resources (team members, materials, etc.) to individual task completions.
